WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:14.472 --> 00:00:15.432 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
Hello.

00:00:15.515 --> 00:00:16.433 position:50% align:center
Welcome.

00:00:16.516 --> 00:00:18.184 position:50% align:center
Do you want a Wonder Egg?

00:00:18.268 --> 00:00:21.104 position:50% align:center
It's hard.

00:00:21.187 --> 00:00:24.524 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA]
What? Are you not sure yet?

00:00:24.607 --> 00:00:25.900 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
Don't hesitate.

00:00:25.984 --> 00:00:29.612 position:50% align:center
Have a little courage
and believe in yourself.

00:00:29.696 --> 00:00:31.865 position:50% align:center
Break the Egg!

00:00:31.948 --> 00:00:34.075 position:50% align:center
Shut up!

00:00:34.159 --> 00:00:36.578 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
It has the thing you want in it.

00:00:36.661 --> 00:00:40.915 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA] You could
say it contains your wish.

00:00:40.999 --> 00:00:44.044 position:50% align:center
If you crack it
in the Egg world...

00:00:44.127 --> 00:00:46.921 position:50% align:center
[ACCA] And if you
clear your mission there...

00:00:49.007 --> 00:00:51.384 position:50% align:center
[AI]
She's a little warm.

00:00:51.468 --> 00:00:54.471 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA] ...you just might
be able to get it back.

00:00:54.554 --> 00:00:55.972 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
Your friend.

00:00:56.056 --> 00:00:57.682 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA]
Your memories.

00:00:57.766 --> 00:01:00.477 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
Your loved one.

00:01:00.560 --> 00:01:02.562 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA]
The first time's free.

00:01:02.645 --> 00:01:04.606 position:50% align:center
After that, bring your wallet.

00:01:04.689 --> 00:01:08.485 position:50% align:center
[ACCA] Hm? You want to know how
we make the Wonder Eggs?

00:01:08.568 --> 00:01:11.196 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA] Sorry, but I'm
afraid that's a trade secret.

00:01:11.279 --> 00:01:12.530 position:50% align:center
We can't just tell you.

00:01:12.614 --> 00:01:13.865 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
I know.

00:01:13.948 --> 00:01:16.951 position:50% align:center
We'll tell you about our
regular customers instead.

00:01:17.035 --> 00:01:20.580 position:50% align:center
A group of four
charming, young girls.

00:01:22.374 --> 00:01:23.500 position:50% align:center
It's our little secret.

00:01:23.583 --> 00:01:26.378 position:50% align:center
A whole world that
no one else knows about.

00:01:26.461 --> 00:01:32.092 position:50% align:center
Huh? A whole world that
no one else knows about.

00:01:32.175 --> 00:01:34.844 position:50% align:center
[ACCA] Why don't you
give their story a listen?

00:01:34.928 --> 00:01:38.556 position:50% align:center
Then, you can make up your own
mind about purchasing an Egg.

00:01:42.143 --> 00:01:44.270 position:50% align:center
[AI]
I'm going out.

00:01:52.320 --> 00:01:55.907 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:01:55.990 --> 00:01:58.159 position:50% align:center
Whoa, crazy.

00:01:58.243 --> 00:02:01.162 position:50% align:center
[ACCA] This isn't reality,
it's closer to a dream.

00:02:01.246 --> 00:02:05.333 position:50% align:center
For right now, we'll simply
refer to it as the "Egg World."

00:02:05.417 --> 00:02:06.835 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA]
It's a place only people

00:02:06.918 --> 00:02:09.212 position:50% align:center
who've broken an
Egg can connect to.

00:02:09.295 --> 00:02:12.424 position:50% align:center
It's strongly influenced
by your mental landscape.

00:02:12.507 --> 00:02:14.634 position:50% align:center
And under very
specific conditions,

00:02:14.718 --> 00:02:17.637 position:50% align:center
you can even share that
special world with other people.

00:02:17.721 --> 00:02:18.638 position:50% align:center
How fun!

00:02:18.722 --> 00:02:20.181 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
You synchronized.

00:02:20.265 --> 00:02:23.059 position:50% align:center
What?

00:02:23.143 --> 00:02:24.477 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
You fell asleep near each other

00:02:24.561 --> 00:02:26.104 position:50% align:center
and at almost the same time.

00:02:26.187 --> 00:02:27.313 position:50% align:center
You're synced.

00:02:27.397 --> 00:02:30.191 position:50% align:center
But then... why aren't
we in my dream instead?

00:02:30.275 --> 00:02:31.359 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA]
You were pulled by

00:02:31.443 --> 00:02:34.070 position:50% align:center
whichever person's
feelings are stronger.

00:02:34.154 --> 00:02:35.613 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
Just break it.

00:02:35.697 --> 00:02:37.824 position:50% align:center
What are you waiting for?

00:02:37.907 --> 00:02:38.867 position:50% align:center
Break what?

00:02:38.950 --> 00:02:41.661 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA]
The Wonder Egg.

00:02:41.745 --> 00:02:43.705 position:50% align:center
[ACCA] See, when you
crack a Wonder Egg,

00:02:43.788 --> 00:02:46.750 position:50% align:center
a girl emerges
from inside of it.

00:02:49.419 --> 00:02:50.754 position:50% align:center
[ACCA] They're girls
who approached death

00:02:50.837 --> 00:02:54.549 position:50% align:center
of their own will and left
their own lives behind.

00:02:54.632 --> 00:02:56.593 position:50% align:center
Now it's up to you
to protect them.

00:02:56.676 --> 00:02:57.969 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA]
But from what?

00:02:58.053 --> 00:03:01.556 position:50% align:center
From things like Seeno Evils
and Wonder Killers.

00:03:01.639 --> 00:03:05.185 position:50% align:center
[laughing]

00:03:07.228 --> 00:03:08.063 position:50% align:center
[AI]
What are they?

00:03:08.146 --> 00:03:10.774 position:50% align:center
You should know!

00:03:10.857 --> 00:03:13.985 position:50% align:center
They're Seeno Evils!

00:03:14.069 --> 00:03:15.445 position:50% align:center
[AI]
What's that?

00:03:15.528 --> 00:03:16.571 position:50% align:center
[KURUMI]
No idea!

00:03:16.654 --> 00:03:17.614 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
First up.

00:03:17.697 --> 00:03:20.325 position:50% align:center
Let's talk about
one of our regulars.

00:03:20.408 --> 00:03:22.744 position:50% align:center
This girl's name is Ai Ohto.

00:03:22.827 --> 00:03:25.622 position:50% align:center
She's a 14-year-old
with heterochromia.

00:03:25.705 --> 00:03:28.291 position:50% align:center
A second year in middle school.

00:03:28.375 --> 00:03:30.960 position:50% align:center
[TAE]
Ai? Your teacher is here.

00:03:31.044 --> 00:03:34.881 position:50% align:center
[SAWAKI] Oh, there's no need
to force her to get up, ma'am.

00:03:34.964 --> 00:03:37.926 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA] When we first met
her, she wasn't going to school.

00:03:38.009 --> 00:03:40.929 position:50% align:center
[ACCA] She says she was
bullied for her heterochromia.

00:03:41.012 --> 00:03:43.723 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA] True,
although that's not the reason

00:03:43.807 --> 00:03:46.434 position:50% align:center
she was skipping
school every day.

00:03:46.518 --> 00:03:48.103 position:50% align:center
[KOITO]
What's that?

00:03:48.186 --> 00:03:49.688 position:50% align:center
Game.

00:03:49.771 --> 00:03:51.731 position:50% align:center
[KOITO]
You like games?

00:03:51.815 --> 00:03:53.900 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
Ai's meeting with Koito Nagase,

00:03:53.983 --> 00:03:55.443 position:50% align:center
a new student in her class,

00:03:55.527 --> 00:03:59.030 position:50% align:center
changed her destiny in a way
she could never anticipate.

00:03:59.114 --> 00:04:00.824 position:50% align:center
[KOITO]
It's mysterious.

00:04:00.907 --> 00:04:02.992 position:50% align:center
You shouldn't try to hide it.

00:04:03.076 --> 00:04:05.620 position:50% align:center
[AI]
I get bullied for it.

00:04:05.704 --> 00:04:07.580 position:50% align:center
A lot.

00:04:09.499 --> 00:04:11.501 position:50% align:center
[KOITO]
It's pretty.

00:04:18.216 --> 00:04:21.428 position:50% align:center
I want you to
be friends with me.

00:04:24.597 --> 00:04:27.851 position:50% align:center
In fact, let's be best friends.

00:04:29.769 --> 00:04:33.773 position:50% align:center
If we could, I'd be happy.

00:04:33.857 --> 00:04:36.818 position:50% align:center
[KOITO]
Me, too.

00:04:36.901 --> 00:04:40.697 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA]
Ai finally made a best friend.

00:04:40.780 --> 00:04:46.202 position:50% align:center
But then one day, she lost
her without any warning.

00:04:46.286 --> 00:04:48.121 position:50% align:center
[AI]
What is all this?

00:04:48.204 --> 00:04:50.206 position:50% align:center
[KOITO]
Just your classic harassment.

00:04:50.290 --> 00:04:52.542 position:50% align:center
But why would anyone
do this to you?

00:04:52.625 --> 00:04:54.502 position:50% align:center
Is it because you're
friends with me?

00:04:54.586 --> 00:04:56.671 position:50% align:center
I doubt it.

00:04:56.755 --> 00:04:58.214 position:50% align:center
I've heard them
say Mister Sawaki

00:04:58.298 --> 00:04:59.799 position:50% align:center
is giving me special treatment.

00:04:59.883 --> 00:05:01.801 position:50% align:center
They're probably just jealous.

00:05:01.885 --> 00:05:03.511 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS laughing]

00:05:03.595 --> 00:05:04.971 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Sorry.

00:05:05.055 --> 00:05:07.682 position:50% align:center
I was scared.

00:05:07.766 --> 00:05:10.185 position:50% align:center
Scared of being left out.

00:05:13.772 --> 00:05:15.732 position:50% align:center
Are you okay?

00:05:21.738 --> 00:05:25.909 position:50% align:center
You got it? Right, Ai?

00:05:25.992 --> 00:05:27.911 position:50% align:center
So, you were scared.

00:05:27.994 --> 00:05:28.995 position:50% align:center
It's okay.

00:05:29.079 --> 00:05:30.205 position:50% align:center
[AI]
I'm really sorry.

00:05:30.288 --> 00:05:31.498 position:50% align:center
It's not your fault.

00:05:31.581 --> 00:05:33.166 position:50% align:center
I know you tried your best.

00:05:33.249 --> 00:05:34.250 position:50% align:center
It's okay.

00:05:34.334 --> 00:05:35.543 position:50% align:center
[AI]
I'm so sorry.

00:05:35.627 --> 00:05:37.587 position:50% align:center
It's all my fault.

00:05:38.755 --> 00:05:42.550 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Because I betrayed you.

00:05:42.634 --> 00:05:45.011 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
Koito Nagase committed suicide.

00:05:45.095 --> 00:05:46.888 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA]
Why'd she die?

00:05:46.971 --> 00:05:48.848 position:50% align:center
What was Ai lacking?

00:05:48.932 --> 00:05:51.518 position:50% align:center
Who pushed Koito toward it?

00:05:51.601 --> 00:05:53.978 position:50% align:center
[ACCA] Ai is fighting
to get back her best friend.

00:05:54.062 --> 00:05:55.438 position:50% align:center
The one she lost.

00:05:55.522 --> 00:05:59.734 position:50% align:center
So, I'm done with pretending
that I don't see anything!

00:05:59.818 --> 00:06:01.444 position:50% align:center
[AI]
I understand.

00:06:01.528 --> 00:06:05.615 position:50% align:center
There was a small part
of me that resented Koito.

00:06:05.699 --> 00:06:09.828 position:50% align:center
We were friends, so why
didn't she just talk to me?

00:06:09.911 --> 00:06:11.121 position:50% align:center
So why?

00:06:11.204 --> 00:06:13.164 position:50% align:center
If she'd asked me
to die with her.

00:06:13.248 --> 00:06:14.708 position:50% align:center
I'd...

00:06:16.668 --> 00:06:20.130 position:50% align:center
[AI yelling]

00:06:20.213 --> 00:06:22.966 position:50% align:center
[AI]
I would have!

00:06:23.049 --> 00:06:27.762 position:50% align:center
Now, I'm really angry!

00:06:30.849 --> 00:06:33.018 position:50% align:center
[ACCA] In order to clear a
mission in the Egg world,

00:06:33.101 --> 00:06:35.937 position:50% align:center
one must defeat what is
known as a Wonder Killer.

00:06:36.021 --> 00:06:40.442 position:50% align:center
They are the symbol of the Egg's
discord, obsession, or trauma.

00:06:41.651 --> 00:06:44.654 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA] While you're in
the Egg world, you're immortal.

00:06:44.738 --> 00:06:47.615 position:50% align:center
[ACCA] Your physical abilities
also dramatically increase.

00:06:47.699 --> 00:06:52.620 position:50% align:center
Now... I'm really
freakin' angry!

00:06:53.872 --> 00:06:55.623 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA]
You may be immortal

00:06:55.707 --> 00:06:57.709 position:50% align:center
but watch out for injuries.

00:06:57.792 --> 00:07:00.295 position:50% align:center
If you come back hurt,
you'll end up like her.

00:07:00.378 --> 00:07:01.588 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
Neiru Aonuma.

00:07:01.671 --> 00:07:04.132 position:50% align:center
[NEIRU]
Here. This is my contact info.

00:07:04.215 --> 00:07:06.760 position:50% align:center
Message me when
you want to change plans.

00:07:06.843 --> 00:07:08.386 position:50% align:center
I'll buy Eggs on odd days,

00:07:08.470 --> 00:07:10.930 position:50% align:center
and you can buy them
on even ones.

00:07:11.014 --> 00:07:13.099 position:50% align:center
That way we don't
have to meet again.

00:07:13.183 --> 00:07:15.352 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA]
Neiru's a girl genius.

00:07:15.435 --> 00:07:19.105 position:50% align:center
She may only be 14,
but she runs her own company.

00:07:19.189 --> 00:07:22.067 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
She's calm, not very talkative,

00:07:22.150 --> 00:07:26.321 position:50% align:center
and doesn't have the most
outgoing of personalities.

00:07:26.404 --> 00:07:28.740 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Here.

00:07:28.823 --> 00:07:30.825 position:50% align:center
[NEIRU]
Thank you.

00:07:30.909 --> 00:07:36.122 position:50% align:center
Whoa. This smells amazing!

00:07:36.206 --> 00:07:37.707 position:50% align:center
It does.

00:07:37.791 --> 00:07:39.376 position:50% align:center
Right?

00:07:44.547 --> 00:07:45.715 position:50% align:center
[NEIRU]
You know...

00:07:45.799 --> 00:07:49.803 position:50% align:center
You're way too trusting
and quick to forgive.

00:07:49.886 --> 00:07:52.180 position:50% align:center
Guess I'm pretty hopeless.

00:07:54.516 --> 00:07:57.435 position:50% align:center
No, you're lovely.

00:07:57.519 --> 00:07:58.728 position:50% align:center
And hopeless.

00:07:58.812 --> 00:08:00.397 position:50% align:center
A healthy mix.

00:08:00.480 --> 00:08:02.857 position:50% align:center
But I believe that we
need more people like you.

00:08:02.941 --> 00:08:05.318 position:50% align:center
If we ever wish to be saved.

00:08:05.402 --> 00:08:08.113 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA] She seems to
have taken a liking to Ai.

00:08:08.196 --> 00:08:12.200 position:50% align:center
But she's a little
too harsh on Rika.

00:08:12.283 --> 00:08:14.703 position:50% align:center
That attitude belongs
in the fifties, fool.

00:08:14.786 --> 00:08:16.287 position:50% align:center
[RIKA] Who you callin'
"fool," fool?

00:08:16.371 --> 00:08:17.330 position:50% align:center
You, the fool.

00:08:17.414 --> 00:08:18.915 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:08:18.998 --> 00:08:21.584 position:50% align:center
Coochy-coochy-coochy-coochy-coo.

00:08:21.668 --> 00:08:23.628 position:50% align:center
Ya ticklish?

00:08:23.712 --> 00:08:26.131 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
Still... Rika has her charms.

00:08:26.214 --> 00:08:27.549 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA]
One of those <i>"tsunderes</i> "?

00:08:27.632 --> 00:08:28.925 position:50% align:center
[NEIRU]
Nuh-uh!

00:08:29.009 --> 00:08:31.928 position:50% align:center
[RIKA]
What about this spot?

00:08:32.012 --> 00:08:35.015 position:50% align:center
[laughing]

00:08:35.098 --> 00:08:36.808 position:50% align:center
[ACCA] The reason why
Neiru is buying Eggs

00:08:36.891 --> 00:08:39.561 position:50% align:center
is because she's fighting
to get back her little sister.

00:08:39.644 --> 00:08:40.770 position:50% align:center
[NEIRU]
Tell me.

00:08:40.854 --> 00:08:42.522 position:50% align:center
Who are you fighting for?

00:08:42.605 --> 00:08:44.524 position:50% align:center
Are you sure it's
not for yourself?

00:08:44.607 --> 00:08:47.652 position:50% align:center
You don't like
who you are, so you go.

00:08:47.736 --> 00:08:49.279 position:50% align:center
Even if you're afraid.

00:08:49.362 --> 00:08:51.448 position:50% align:center
You want to change
the self you hate.

00:08:51.531 --> 00:08:54.075 position:50% align:center
It's not that I want to,
I just have to is all.

00:08:54.159 --> 00:08:55.452 position:50% align:center
And for what?

00:08:55.535 --> 00:08:57.662 position:50% align:center
For someone selfish enough to--

00:08:57.746 --> 00:08:59.748 position:50% align:center
Selfish enough
to kill themselves?

00:08:59.831 --> 00:09:02.459 position:50% align:center
[AI] Rika, Neiru's trying
to save her sister.

00:09:02.542 --> 00:09:04.377 position:50% align:center
You're wrong.

00:09:04.461 --> 00:09:06.171 position:50% align:center
My sister stabbed me.

00:09:06.254 --> 00:09:07.797 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:09:07.881 --> 00:09:10.759 position:50% align:center
[NEIRU] Then, she ran away
and jumped off a bridge.

00:09:10.842 --> 00:09:12.469 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Stabbed you?

00:09:12.552 --> 00:09:15.889 position:50% align:center
[NEIRU] That's what they told me
when I woke up in the ICU.

00:09:15.972 --> 00:09:18.850 position:50% align:center
[RIKA] Then you've got
even less of a reason.

00:09:18.933 --> 00:09:22.062 position:50% align:center
[NEIRU] The scar aches
and keeps me awake at night.

00:09:22.145 --> 00:09:23.605 position:50% align:center
Or it did.

00:09:23.688 --> 00:09:27.025 position:50% align:center
But the pain has faded a little
since I started coming here.

00:09:27.108 --> 00:09:31.404 position:50% align:center
When I try to forget her,
my scar aches, like a curse.

00:09:31.488 --> 00:09:34.115 position:50% align:center
That's why I go.

00:09:34.199 --> 00:09:36.826 position:50% align:center
No other reason.

00:09:36.910 --> 00:09:39.287 position:50% align:center
It's for me.

00:09:39.371 --> 00:09:41.706 position:50% align:center
[AOI]
Girls grow up into women.

00:09:41.790 --> 00:09:45.335 position:50% align:center
It's a miraculous thing,
much like a butterfly emerging.

00:09:45.418 --> 00:09:47.671 position:50% align:center
One, brief moment.

00:09:49.547 --> 00:09:51.257 position:50% align:center
[AOI]
You're very pretty, you know.

00:09:51.341 --> 00:09:52.676 position:50% align:center
Why don't you die, too?

00:09:52.759 --> 00:09:55.303 position:50% align:center
Why not end it all when
you're at your most beautiful?

00:09:55.387 --> 00:09:56.471 position:50% align:center
What sense is there in clinging

00:09:56.554 --> 00:09:57.889 position:50% align:center
--to a meaningless life?
--This isn't good.

00:09:57.972 --> 00:10:01.851 position:50% align:center
Hey, answer me:
Why don't you die, too?

00:10:01.935 --> 00:10:03.895 position:50% align:center
Why... don't you?

00:10:03.978 --> 00:10:05.855 position:50% align:center
Tell me!

00:10:07.982 --> 00:10:09.150 position:50% align:center
[CURLS]
Tell us!

00:10:09.234 --> 00:10:12.112 position:50% align:center
Guess I'm gonna have
to blow your mind, too.

00:10:12.195 --> 00:10:14.239 position:50% align:center
[gunshots]

00:10:14.322 --> 00:10:17.158 position:50% align:center
[NEIRU]
"Why don't I die, too?" Huh.

00:10:17.242 --> 00:10:21.830 position:50% align:center
